Roster as of the end of the 200708 WHL season

NHL alumni
Image:Getz-reach.jpg thumb 200px right Ryan Getzlaf played four seasons with the Hitmen between 2001 and 2005.
Thirty-four players have been selected from the Hitmen roster at the NHL Entry Draft.cite book  editor=Flett, Cory and Watts, Jessie  title=200708 WHL Guide  publisher=Western Hockey League  pages=41  Of those, nine players were selected in the first round.  The highest drafted players in club history were Pavel Brendl 1999 NHL Entry Draft 1999 and Andrew Ladd 2004 NHL Entry Draft 2004.  Both players were selected fourth overall.  Four players were selected in the 2007 NHL Entry Draft 2007 draft: Karl Alzner 5th overall to Washington Capitals Washington, Alex Plante 15th overall to Edmonton Oilers Edmonton, Brett Sonne 3rd round to St. Louis Blues hockey St. Louis and Carson McMillan 7th round to Minnesota Wild Minnesota.cite web  url=http://www.hitmenhockey.com/cgi-bin/news/comments.cgi?type=newsroom&file_num=0000000998  title=Four Calgary Hitmen selected in 2007 NHL Entry Draft  accessdate=2008-02-24  date=2007-06-23  publisher=Calgary Hitmen Hockey Club

Twenty-one former Hitmen players have gone on to play in the National Hockey League.4 cite book  editor=Reghenas, Kip and Curle, Brad  title=The Zone  edition=10  series=4  year=200708  publisher=Calgary Hitmen Hockey Club  pages=40   The first was Ryan Bast, who played two games with the Philadelphia Flyers in 1998-99 NHL season 199899.cite web url=http://www.hockeydb.com/ihdb/stats/pdisplay.php3?pid=23553 title=Ryan Bast player profile work=The Internet Hockey Database accessdate=2008-02-23  In 2006 Stanley Cup Finals 2006, Ladd became the first Hitmen graduate to win the Stanley Cup, doing so with the Hurricanes.cite web  url=http://www.hitmenhockey.com/cgi-bin/news/comments.cgi?type=newsroom&file_num=0000000428  title=Andrew Ladd becomes first Hitmen alumni to win the Stanley Cup  accessdate=2008-02-24  author=Brownlee, Robin  date=2006-06-20  publisher=Calgary Hitmen Hockey Club The feat duplicated one year later by Ladd's former teammate, Ryan Getzlaf with the Anaheim Ducks.cite web  url=http://www.hitmenhockey.com/cgi-bin/news/comments.cgi?type=newsroom&file_num=0000001014  title=Getzlaf ready to take Stanley Cup home  accessdate=2008-02-24  date=2007-07-23  publisher=Calgary Hitmen Hockey Club One former player has had his number retired by the Hitmen.  Brad Moran ice hockey Brad Moran, the franchise's all-time leading scorer, had his #20 retired in 2005.cite web  url=http://www.hitmenhockey.com/cgi-bin/news/comments.cgi?type=newsroom&file_num=0000000232  title= Hitmen honour all-time leading point scorer Brad Moran on February 25th  accessdate=2008-02-24  date=2005-02-08  publisher=Calgary Hitmen Hockey Club

