Head coaches
Dean Clark has been the most successful coach for the Hitmen.  Clark coached 333 regular season games from October 1996 until the end of the 200001 season.cite web  url=http://www.hitmenhockey.com/cgi-bin/news/comments.cgi?type=newsroom&file_num=0000000046  title=Hitmen Make Coaching Change  accessdate=2008-04-15  date=2001-06-07  publisher=Calgary Hitmen Hockey Club  He was the winningest coach in the Western Hockey League during that time, and was named the Canadian Hockey League's Brian Kilrea Coach of the Year Award Coach of the Year in 199798.cite web  url=http://www.canoe.ca/WHLNews0102/jul17_clark.html  title=Dean Clark named Brandon Wheat Kings' new head coach   accessdate=2008-04-15  date=2001-07-17  publisher=canoe.ca  Clark led the Hitmen to three division titles, two regular season titles, one Ed Chynoweth Cup league championship, and the Memorial Cup final.cite web  url=http://www.legendsofhockey.net:8080/LegendsOfHockey/jsp/SearchPlayer.jsp?player=12278  title=Dean Clark profile   accessdate=2008-04-15  publisher=Hockey Hall of Fame  Kelly Kisio has been the team's head coach since the 200405 season, a role he shared with Dean Evason in his first year at the helm of the Hitmen.cite web  url=http://www.hitmenhockey.com/mediareleases/MEDIA_REL/comments.cgi?discussion_no=1&subject_no=193  title=Kelly Kisio and Dean Evason Take Over Coaching Duties  date=2004-05-18  accessdate=2008-04-15  publisher=Calgary Hitmen Hockey Club Kisio has been the team's general manager since 199899.cite web  url=http://www.hitmenhockey.com/team/staff.html#kisio  title=Staff  Kelly Kisio   accessdate=2008-04-15  publisher=Calgary Hitmen Hockey Club


